    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Lower the electronegativity, higher is the tendency of the atom/group to donate its pair of electrons and hence higher is nucleophilicity. Now among $\\mathrm{F}(4.0), \\mathrm{O}(3.5), \\mathrm{N}(3.0)$ and $\\mathrm{C}(2.5), \\mathrm{C}$ has the lowest electronegativity and hence, $\\mathrm{CH}_3^{-}$ has highest nucleophilicity.</p>",
